public class AbstractDispatchAction
extends org.apache.struts.actions.DispatchAction

This is an abstract subclass of org.apache.struts.actions.DispatchAction and extends it by permission checking for user actions.

Method Detail

isAllowedToProcess

protected boolean isAllowedToProcess(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request,
                                     java.lang.String processName)
Checks if a user is allowed to request some specific action respective process. Returns true, if so and false if not. Permissions are set set in AdministrationAction

Parameters:
request - The actual servlet request of the action
processName - the process name
Returns:
true, if the user is allowed, false if not
